<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Get Wrong</h2>

  <h3>Assuming a Mix Creates Succession Automatically</h3>
  <p>
    Most mixes are designed for single harvest windows.
  </p>

  <h3>Planting Everything at Once</h3>
  <p>
    This defeats the purpose of succession planting.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Matching Mixes to Climate</h3>
  <p>
    Some mixes perform differently depending on temperature and season length.
  </p>

  <h3>Relying Only on Mixes</h3>
  <p>
    The best results usually come from combining mixes with individual plantings.
  </p>
</section>

